{"image_id": "CINF_2012_page_67", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Cincinnati Financial Corporation – 2012 10-K - 65", "bbox": [461.2, 1600.4, 840.9, 1622.7]}, {"text": "Specialty Packages", "bbox": [150.0, 57.6, 349.8, 89.6]}, {"text": "Specialty packages net written premiums and earned premiums rose in 2012, primarily due to lower ceded", "bbox": [150.0, 594.1, 1135.0, 621.7]}, {"text": "premiums. In 2011, ceded premiums included $10 million to reinstate coverage layers of our property", "bbox": [150.0, 618.1, 1085.4, 645.8]}, {"text": "catastrophe reinsurance treaty. New business written premiums from agencies accounted for less than", "bbox": [150.0, 641.9, 1100.2, 669.5]}, {"text": "$1 million of the $16 million increase in net written premiums, in part reflecting our efforts to increase", "bbox": [150.0, 665.9, 1079.1, 693.5]}, {"text": "price adequacy.", "bbox": [150.0, 689.9, 302.8, 717.5]}, {"text": "The 2012 total loss and loss expense ratio improved 49.3 percentage points primarily due to a 33.7-point", "bbox": [150.0, 720.2, 1119.3, 747.8]}, {"text": "decrease in catastrophe losses. The 2012 current accident year loss and loss expense ratio before", "bbox": [150.0, 744.2, 1064.5, 771.8]}, {"text": "catastrophe losses also improved, compared with accident year 2011, largely due to higher earned", "bbox": [150.0, 768.2, 1064.2, 795.8]}, {"text": "premiums that included higher pricing. In 2011, we began fully using predictive modeling tools for auto,", "bbox": [150.0, 791.9, 1100.4, 819.6]}, {"text": "general liability and property coverages for some commercial package accounts included in specialty", "bbox": [150.0, 815.9, 1082.7, 843.6]}, {"text": "packages. In 2012, we began using predictive modeling tools to improve our pricing precision for certain", "bbox": [150.0, 840.0, 1111.7, 867.6]}, {"text": "additional business policies included in our specialty packages line of business. Initiatives for our property", "bbox": [150.0, 864.0, 1126.8, 891.6]}, {"text": "book of business, described in the commercial property section above, should also benefit our specialty", "bbox": [150.0, 888.0, 1107.5, 915.6]}, {"text": "packages line of business. We believe these initiatives will improve profitability over time.", "bbox": [150.0, 911.7, 974.5, 939.3]}, {"text": "The 2011 total loss and loss expense ratio rose 51.2 percentage points primarily due to a 39.3-point", "bbox": [150.0, 942.0, 1073.7, 969.6]}, {"text": "increase in catastrophe losses. It also rose from other weather-related losses that were not identified as part", "bbox": [150.0, 966.0, 1150.4, 993.6]}, {"text": "of designated catastrophe events for the property casualty industry, typically referred to as noncatastrophe", "bbox": [150.0, 990.0, 1134.9, 1017.6]}, {"text": "weather losses. The effect of the $10 million in premiums ceded to reinstate coverage layers of our property", "bbox": [150.0, 1014.0, 1146.4, 1041.6]}, {"text": "catastrophe reinsurance treaty increased the 2011 ratio by 8.4 percentage points.", "bbox": [150.0, 1038.0, 906.3, 1065.6]}, {"text": "The 2011 current accident year loss and loss expense ratio before catastrophe losses also increased,", "bbox": [150.0, 1068.0, 1090.7, 1095.6]}, {"text": "compared with accident year 2010, largely due to noncatastrophe weather and the effects of", "bbox": [150.0, 1092.0, 1005.0, 1119.6]}, {"text": "reinstatement premiums.", "bbox": [150.0, 1116.0, 390.8, 1143.6]}, {"text": "(Dollars in millions)", "bbox": [96.4, 94.5, 202.4, 111.5]}, {"text": "2012", "bbox": [622.3, 113.0, 654.8, 134.4]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [730.9, 113.6, 763.4, 134.8]}, {"text": "2010", "bbox": [839.5, 113.6, 872.0, 134.8]}, {"text": "Specialty packages:", "bbox": [96.8, 133.6, 224.3, 154.7]}, {"text": "Net written premiums", "bbox": [96.8, 153.6, 249.7, 174.7]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [588.5, 153.3, 596.5, 174.7]}, {"text": "153", "bbox": [644.6, 153.8, 669.0, 175.3]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [697.1, 153.6, 705.1, 17